---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Architecture">
  <h1>Architecture</h1>

  <p>Agent Forge is organized around a single orchestration loop driven by LLM-generated code, tests, and refinements.</p>

  <h2>System Overview</h2>
  <pre><code>Natural Language Description
         |
   LoopController
    |          |
 Generator  ---- (on failure)
    |
 Agent File (single .ts)
    |
 Evaluator
    | TestGenerator (LLM auto-generates test cases)
    | TestRunner (exec agent against tests)
    | LLMJudge (semantic quality scoring)
    | ScoreReport
    |
 QualityGate: pass? - OutputAdapter - write to target
            fail? - Refiner - rewrite - loop</code></pre>

  <h2>Components</h2>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Component</th><th>Role</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>Generator</code></td><td>NL description to AgentSchema to TypeScript agent file</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>TestGenerator</code></td><td>LLM generates k diverse test cases from agent spec</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>Evaluator</code></td><td>Runs agent against tests + LLM judge to ScoreReport</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>Refiner</code></td><td>Failure report to targeted rewrite of agent</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>QualityGate</code></td><td>Pass/fail threshold with coverage and generalization checks</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>LoopController</code></td><td>State machine orchestrating the full loop</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>Registry</code></td><td>SQLite persistence: agents, versions, eval history</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>Runtime</code></td><td>Agent execution via bun:eval subprocess</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>NestedExecutor</code></td><td>Multi-agent call graph with depth limit + cycle detection</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>OutputAdapter</code></td><td>Writes finished agents to Claude Skills or Standalone format</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>State Machine</h2>
  <pre><code>IDLE - GENERATING - EVALUATING - REFINING - (loop or DONE)
                                          |
                                        FAILED</code></pre>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>IDLE</strong> — Initial state, waiting for task</li>
    <li><strong>GENERATING</strong> — LLM producing initial agent code</li>
    <li><strong>EVALUATING</strong> — Running tests + LLM judge</li>
    <li><strong>REFINING</strong> — LLM rewriting agent from failure report</li>
    <li><strong>DONE</strong> — Agent passed QualityGate</li>
    <li><strong>FAILED</strong> — Max iterations reached without passing</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>LLM Backend Abstraction</h2>
  <p>All LLM calls go through <code>LLMBackend</code> interface. Currently supported:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Ollama</strong> (default) — Local, no API costs</li>
    <li><strong>OpenAI</strong> — GPT-4o, GPT-4o-mini, o3</li>
    <li><strong>Anthropic</strong> — Via OpenAI-compatible adapter</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Set via environment variables — no code changes needed.</p>

  <h2>Registry Schema</h2>
  <pre><code>agents
  -- id, name, description, latest_version

agent_versions
  -- id, agent_id, version, code

eval_runs
  -- id, agent_version_id, iteration, test_pass_rate,
     judge_score, composite_score, passed, failure_report

test_cases
  -- id, agent_id, input_json, expected_schema,
     traced_to (intent clause), diversity_score</code></pre>
</Layout>
